<HEAD><TITLE>Equinox International-Air Filter</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="images/a_bkg4.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800040" ALINK="#000000">
<a name="top">


<MAP NAME="a_bar1">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="404,0,465,114" HREF="index.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="347,0,400,114" HREF="qcform.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="294,1,344,114" HREF="ghindex.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="239,0,290,114" HREF="whatsnew.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="181,0,237,114" HREF="opportun.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="128,1,179,114" HREF="products.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="72,2,125,112" HREF="company.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="0,4,68,111" HREF="#top">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="0,0,466,114" HREF="index.html">
</MAP>
<!--Map by Web Hotspots 2.0  http://www.cris.com/~automata/ -->

<IMG SRC="images/h_title1.jpg" ALT="Equinox International" WIDTH=483 HEIGHT=108 BORDER=0>
<center>
<font size=+3 color=#004F9D><STRONG>Equinox Air Filtration Systems</STRONG></font><br>
</center>

<CENTER><img src="images/01.jpg" ALT="Air Group Picture" align=right hspace=10 vspace=15></CENTER><P>
Most people are aware that outdoor air pollution can damage their health, but they may not know that indoor air pollution can be even more dangerous. The construction of well-sealed buildings with reduced ventilation rates and the use of household cleaners, pesticides, and personal care products all contribute to serious health problems. Studies show indoor air can be eight to ten times more toxic than outdoor air. Equinox Air Filtration Systems reduce the amount of pollutants and potentially hazardous materials we are exposed to whether at home, at work, or in the car, creating a healthier environment for ourselves and our families. All of our air filtration systems are made from superior quality, heavy duty materials and come with an excellent warranty, which is validated when the warranty card is sent in to Equinox.<P>



<font size=+1>EQ-100 Portable Air Filtration System</font><BR>
Designed to be used away from home, the EQ-100 Portable Air Filtration System is ideal for use in vehicles, hotel rooms, or anywhere that indoor air quality is a concern. This compact unit draws polluted air through a highly effective three-stage filtration system and expels clean air in all directions around the circumference of the unit for maximum coverage. The first stage filter removes large dust particles and absorbs noxious fumes and odors. The second stage filter attracts and holds submicron dust particles from the air, and the third stage filter absorbs gaseous contaminants. Two adapters are included with this unit, a 12 volt dc for cars and a 110 or 230 volt ac transformer for indoor use. The EQ-100 Portable Air Filtration System has a one-year pro rata warranty.<P>

<font size=+1>EQ-1000 Tabletop and EQ-2000 Floor Model Air Filtration Systems</font><BR>
These outstanding home filtration systems effectively remove 99.9% of particulate pollution using a three-stage filtration process. In the first stage, a carbon pre-filter helps to eliminate fumes, dust, odors, and smoke. The second stage consists of a 3,000 grade HEPA (High Efficiency Particulate Air) filter that eliminates pollen, bacteria, mold spores, attached viruses, animal dander, and radon progeny. It is effective on particles down to 0.3 microns in size, which is approximately 250 times smaller than a human hair. Finally, in the third stage, a carbon blanket removes additional chemicals, fumes, and odors. Both units have an external baked powder-coated epoxy steel housing that comes in basic black and off-white.  Equinox provides a one-year pro rata warranty from the date of purchase for complete parts and labor against defects in materials or workmanship and a two-year pro rata warranty on the HEPA filter, providing for normal home or office use.<P>

<font size=+1>EQ-1000 Tabletop Model</font>
<ul>
<li>Air flow rate of 50 to 175 cubic feet per minute
<LI>Maximum hourly air flow of 10,500 cubic feet
<LI>Air turnover per hour--875% (150 square foot room)
<LI>Recommended maximum service area --200 square feet
<li>50 square feet of 3,000 Grade HEPA borosilicate filter media
</ul><P>

<font size=+1>EQ-2000 Floor Model</font>
<ul>
<li>Air flow rate of 50 to 225 cubic feet per minute
<LI>Maximum hourly air flow of 13,500 cubic feet
<LI>Air turnover per hour -- 1,125% (150 square foot room)
<LI>Recommended maximum service area -- 400 square feet
<LI>100 square feet of 3,000 Grade HEPA borosilicate filter media
</ul><P>


For more information on how to order products or
to become an independent Equinox representative, please complete our online 
<a href="qcform.html">Inquiry Form</a>.<p>

