</ul>
</ul>
</b>
<hr noshade>

<a href="../slang/home.html">
<img align=left src="/graphics/logos/slang_logo_sm.jpg" border = 0>
<b>On-Line Dictionary of Street Drug Slang</a></b>

Indiana Prevention Resource Center's collection of street drug slang,
based in part upon a list of 2000+ drug slang terms developed by the
Indiana Prevention Resource Center with more than 1000 additions from
the National Drugs & Crime Clearinghouse files.<br>

<hr>
<a href="../acronym/home.html">
<img align=right src="/graphics/logos/acronym_logo_sm.jpg" border = 0>
<b>Directory of Alcohol, Tobacco, and Other Drug Abbreviations and
Acronyms </a></b>

Indiana Prevention Resource Center's directory of ATOD abbreviations
and acronyms.  Learn how to decode the "alphabet soup" jargon of the
field.<br> <p><br>

<hr>
<p>
<img align=left src="/graphics/logos/legalize.gif" border = 0>
<a name = "legalize">
<h3>Arguments Against Drug Legalization</h3>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <a href=http://www.usdoj.gov/dea/pubs/legaliz/contents.htm>Speaking
Out Against Legalization</a> (U.S. DEA Outline for Debate)<br>
<li> <a href=http://www.lec.org/Drug_Watch/Public/>Drug Watch, International
Public Access Documents </a><br>
<li> <a href=http://www.mdle.com/legdrugs.htm>Legalization Is Giving Up </a><br>
<li> <a href="/publications/iprc/misc/smokescreen.html">The Marijuana
Smokescreen </a> (IPRC Publication)<br>
<li> <a href=http://www.intellinet.com/~aclight/kim/drg_lgl.html>The
Drug Legalization Debate:  A pharmacology professor's views.</a><br>
<li> <a href=http://www.elks.org/drugs/pridepo1.html>PRIDE's Position Paper Against Legalization of Drugs</a>

</ul>
<hr>
<p>
<img align="right" src="/graphics/logos/drugtest.jpg">
<a name = "testing">
<h3>Drug Testing</h3>
<p>
NOTE:  Linking to commercial and other sites does not imply endorsement of products, services, or content.
<ul>
<li> <a href= http://www.nist.gov/item/NIST_Methods_and_Standards_for_Drugs-of-Abuse_Testing.html>Drug Testing Standards (National Institute of Standards & Technology)
</a><br>
<li> <a href=http://www.stpt.usf.edu/journal/index.html>International Journal
of Drug Testing </a> an on-line journal
<li> <a href= "/publications/ncadi/primer/drugtest.htm">Drug Testing in the Workplace
(NCADI)</a><br>

<li> <a href=http://www.health.org/pubs/urine/umenu.htm>Urine Specimen Collection Handbook
for Federal Workplace Drug Testing Programs </a>

<li> <a href=http://www.olympic.org/medical/fedop.html>International Olympic Committee -
Fight Against Doping </a>  Olympic drug testing information

<li> <a href=http://www.courttv.com/cases/vernonia/vernonia.htm>Court TV Cases -
Vernonia Case </a> (U.S. Supreme Court ruling on suspicionless drug tests for
public school athletes)

<li> <a href=http://www.wa.gov/courts/educate/lessons/drugtest.htm>Drug 
Testing in Schools Lesson Plan </a>

<li> <a href=http://www.sfgate.com/examiner/prev/examiner-062695/NEWS-26790.html>Student
Athlete Drug Testing Upheld </a> San Francisco <i>Examiner</i>

<li> <a href= http://www.wpa.org/nacs/>National Association of Collection Sites
[for Drug Testing] </a>

<li> <a href= http://www.mrocc.com>Medical Review Officer Certification
Council</a> (drug testing reviews)

<li> <a href=http://www.lec.org/Drug_Watch/Public/Documents/DWDTPOS.html>Drug Watch International Position Statement on Drug Testing</a>

<li> <a href=http://www.nida.nih.gov/NIDA_Notes/NNVol10N5/Sweat.html>Sweat Testing May Prove Useful (Article, NIDA)</a>

<li> <a href=http://www.fda.gov/bbs/topics/ANSWERS/ANS00674>Drug Sweat Patch Testing</a>
</a><br>

<li> <a href= http://perry.gulfnet.com/advertisers/drug_testing/drug1.htm>
Mail-In Self-Tests for Drugs of Abuse (Windy Hills Professional Laboratories)</a><br>

<li> <a href= http://htrac.com/htrac.html>
Hair Testing for Illicit Drug Use</a><br>(Hair Trac Technology)


<li> <a href="/druginfo/dotrules.html">
U.S. Department of Transportation Alcohol and Drug Testing Rules</a><br>
(Federal Highway Administration)


     
</ul>

<hr>

