<!-- title image end -->

<h1>Drug Photo Menu</h1>
<p>
<img src="/graphics/icons/bar3.gif"></center>
<p>
<p>

This menu will allow prevention professionals to access color photographs 
of drugs and drug-related topics that can be downloaded and used in 
locally-produced prevention materials, such as overhead transparencies, 
slides, posters, and handout materials.
<p>
Users of Netscape can download a graphic by simply touching the graphic
with their cursor, and then "clicking" on the right hand mouse button, 
which will reveal a graphics menu.  Just select "save this image" and
then follow the instructions.  Users of other browser software should
consult the documentation for their browser for downloading instructions 
if using the right hand mouse button does not work.
<p>
All of the photos linked below appear to be in the public domain, or are 
presented in menus that imply permission to download.  To be sure that 
no copyright laws are violated, we recommend securing the permission of 
the Website before using any graphic beyond the "fair educational use" 
allowed by the federal copyright laws.
<p>
<ul>
<li> <a href="deapics.html">Drug Photos from the U.S. Drug Enforcement
Administration </a>
<li> <a href="iprcpics.html">Drug Photos from the IPRC Website </a>
<li> <a href="ncadipics.html">Drug Photos from the NCADI Website </a>
<li> <a href=http://www.hyperreal.com/drugs/psychedelics/lsd/lick.this.screen.html>LSD
Images from the Hyperreal Archive </a> NOTE: Not a "prevention" site.  We do
not endorse the editorial content on this site.
<li> <a href="http://www.winternet.com/~publish/photos.htm"> Drug Photo Archive</a> from Publishers Group, (free use for no-profit activites)
<li> <a href="http://www.health.org/pubs/makepub/gindex.htm"> Miscellaneous Graphics from NCADI Website</a>
<li> <a href="http://www.yahoo.com/Computers_and_Internet/Multimedia/Pictures/Clip_Art/"> Miscellaneous Clip Art from Yahoo</a>
<li> <a href="http://sunsite.unc.edu/gio/iconbrowser/"> Icon Browser </a>(Search the Web for Icons)

</ul>
<p>
                
<p>
