<h2>Tobacco Information</h2>
      
       
<p>
<h3>Tobacco Facts</h3>
<p>
<ul>

<li> <a href=http://www.drugs.indiana.edu/pubs/factline/tobac.html>
Factline on  TOBACCO</a> (Indiana PRC)
       

<li> <a href="http://oncolink.upenn.edu/causeprevent/smoking/">
Smoking, Tobacco and Cancer (Oncolink) </A>

</ul>

<hr>
      



      
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<h3>HOT LINKS to Internet Tobacco Sites </h3>
<p>
<ul>

<li> <a href="http://iumeded.med.iupui.edu/tobacco/tobacco.htm">
Tobacco Control Resource Center </a> I.U. School of Medicine <br>
many Indiana tobacco links

<li> <a href=http://www.ash.org/ash/>
Action on Smoking and Health (ASH)</a><br>
A leading national nonsmokers' rights activist organization.  
	ASH takes a major role in litigation and regulatory petitions 
	to protect nonsmokers' rights.<br>

<li> <a href=http://www.ash.org.uk/>
Action on Smoking and Health - United Kingdom </a> <br>
Great Britain's version of ASH <br>


<li> <a href=http://www.ccsg.ca/>
Canadian Council on Smoking and Health </a>

<li> <a href=http://www.no-smoke.org/>
American's for Nonsmokers' Rights </a>

<li> <a href=http://galen.library.ucsf.edu/tobacco/>
Tobacco Control Archives</a><br>
Archive of papers related to tobacco control initiatives, especially in California; host site of the 
collection of the incrminating Brown & Williamson Tobacco Company documents that have 
receives heavy media attention.<br>

<li> <a href=http://www.cdc.gov/nccdphp/osh/tobacco.htm>
Centers for Disease Control Tobacco Use Information Page</a><br>
     Facts, statistics, directory of information sources, publications, etc.

<li> <a href=http://www.cancer.org/>
American Cancer Society </a>

<li> <a href=http://www.amhrt.org/>American Heart Association</a>

<li> <a href=http://www-uicc.who.ch/toba.html>
International Union Against Cancer (UICC) - Tobacco & Cancer Page</a><br>

 <li> <a href="http://www.ccsh.ca/">Canadian Council on
Smoking and Health </a>

<li> <a href="http://www.kickbutt.org/">
Kickbutt.org </a> Washington DOC's Anti-Smoking Website

 <li> <a href=http://www.courttv.com/library/tobacco>CourtTV Tobacco Cases </a>

 <li> <a href=http://www.cs.brown.edu/people/lsh/smoking.html>Smoking from All Sides Page </a><br>
 Extensive links, comprehensive smoking information from both sides 

<li> <a href= http://www.ama-assn.org>American Medical Association</a>  [You will 
be asked to register for free and select a password before using this link]</br>

<li> <a href="http://www.tobacco.org/">     
Tobacco Issues BBS</a><br>
     Miscellaneous information on tobacco control issues.

<li> <a href=http://www.autonomy.com/smoke.htm>The Master Anti-Smoking Page </a>
hundreds of links to anti-smoking information

 <li> <a href=http://world.std.com/~batteryb/>The BADvertising Institute </a><br>
humorous approach to debunking tobacco advertising

<li> <a href=http://www.bcm.tmc.edu/doc/>DOC:  Doctors Ought to Care</a><br>
Medical activist organization.

<li> <a href="http://www.gate.net/~jcannon/tobacco.html">
Tobacco Industry Documents </a> <br>
"smoking gun" documents on-line that document industry deception
 
<li> <a href="http://www.discovery.com/DCO/doc/1012/world/history/cigarettes/cigarettegallery.html">
Old-Time Cigarette Advertising Gallery </a> <br>
from the Discovery Channel Online

<li> <a href="http://www.smokescreen.org">
Smokescreen Tobacco Control Network </a>


<li> <a href=http://www.boutell.com/infact>
INFACT Stop Marketing Tobacco to Children Campaign</a><br>
     Media campaign against markting tobacco products to children; other tobacco issues

<li> <a href=http://www.boutell.com/infact/gasp/gasp.html>
New Jersey GASP - Group Aainst Smokers' Pollution</a><br>
     Non-smokers rights organization, directory of smokefree dining and other issues

<li> <a href=http://www.fda.gov/cgi-bin/bbs-form.pl?keywords=tobacco&DAYS= 
&CONTEXT=Search+in+al>
FDA Statements on Tobacco from Tobacco BBS</a><br>
     U.S. Food and Drug Administration official statements on tobacco and nicotine addiction

<li> <a href=http://hinet.medlib.arizona.edu/~pubhlth/tobac.htm>
NicNet:  The Arizona Nicotine & Tobacco Network</a><br>
     Tobacco and Smoking prevention and activism resources

<li> <a href=http://www.quitnet.org>The QuitNet (Massachusetts Tobacco Control Program)</a> 

<li> <a href=http://www.hookup.net/~tpolevoy>NO PATSY - National Organization of People Attacking Tobacco Sales to Youth (Canada)</a>

<li> <a href=http://charlotte.med.nyu.edu/woodr/tobacco.html>Tobacco Links</a>

<li> <a href="http://iumeded.med.iupui.edu/tobacco/assist.htm">
ASSIST - American Stop Smoking Intervention Study - Indiana </a>

<li> <a href="http"//www.boutel.com/infact/faces">
Face the Faces:  Victims of the Tobacco Industry </a>

</ul>
