<TITLE>Indiana-Drug-related Death Stats -- Indiana PRC</TITLE>

<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<h2>Indiana Together:  Strategies for achieiving a drug-free Indiana</h2>
<h3>Problem Indicators Table #6</h3>
<hr>
<p>
<b>6. Average age of first use of alcohol by school students.
<p>
<p>
The Indiana data shows no significant change from 1992 to 1994.  This data
was not collected for reporting prior to 1992.  This data is available
locally for school districts which participate in the "Alcohol, Tobacco,
and Other Drug Use by Indiana Children and Adolescents" 1994 Survey.
<p>
<center>
<table>

<tr><td> 1998 Nat'l Avg.</td><td>13.1 years</td></tr>
<tr><td> 1992 State Avg.</td><td>13.0 years</td></tr>
<tr><td> 1993 State Avg.</td><td>13.0 years</td></tr>
<tr><td> 1994 State Avg.</td><td>13.0 years</td></tr>

</table>
</center>
<p>
<p>
Source:  Indiana Prevention Resource Center
