<H2>Federal Government Resources for ATOD Prevention</H2>

<p>

<b>

<ul>
<LI> <a href=http://www.health.org>
National Clearinghouse for Alcohol and Drug Information (NCADI)</a><br>
The nation's primary information clearinghouse for consumer information about alcohol and 
other drugs.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.samhsa.gov>
Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA)</a><br>
Agency that coordinates AOD and Mental Health Services centers (Center for Substance Abuse 
Prevention, Center for Substance Abuse Treatment, and Center for Mental Health Services) 
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.nida.nih.gov>
National Institute on Drug Abuse (NIDA)</a><br>
The nation's research institute for drug abuse issues.  Part of the National Institutes of Health.
<p>
<li> <a href=http://www.niaaa.nih.gov>
National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism </a>
<p>
<li> <a href=http://www.nida.nih.gov/NIDA_Notes/NNIndex.html>
<i>NIDA Notes </i>Newsletter<br>
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.covesoft.com/csap.html>
CSAP Technical Assistance to Communities</a><br>
Technical assistance contractor provided by the Center for Substance Abuse Prevention
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.cdc.gov>
Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)</a><br>
The nation's lead agency in disease control and prevention.  A part of the U.S. Public Health 
Service.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.fda.gov>
Food and Drug Administration (FDA)</a><br>
The nation's food and drug regulatory agency.  Has primary jurisdiction over prescription and 
over-the-counter drug regulation.  Presently exploring regulation of tobacco as an addictive 
drug.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://phs.os.dhhs.gov/phs/phs.html>
U.S. Public Health Service (USPHS)</a><br>
Main WWW Home page for the U.S Public Health Service
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://nhic-nt.health.org/>
National Health Information Center (NHIC)</a><br>
The nation's central clearinghouse for health information for the public.  This page contains 
many "hot links" to health-related information sources.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.cdc.gov/nchswww/nchshome.htm>
National Center for Health Statistics WWW Server</a><br>
Note:  Adobe Acrobat Reader software (may be downloaded free from this site) is required to 
view and print some of the reports available at this site.
<p>
<li> <a href=http://www.ustreas.gov/treasury/bureaus/atf/atf.html>
Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, and Firearms (U.S. Department of the Treasury) </a>
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://odphp.oash.dhhs.gov/>
Office of Disease Prevention and Health Promotion</a><br>
The nation's policy-level office concerned with disease prevention and health promotion.  Part 
of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.nih.gov/home.html>
National Institutes of Health (NIH)</a><br>
The nation's medical research organization, coordinating federal medical and health-related 
research programs.  Provides research (not program) grants.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.os.dhhs.gov/>
U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS)</a><br>
Main WWW Home page for the Department of Health and Human Services
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.ed.gov>
U.S. Department of Education (USDOE)</a><br>
The nation's education agency, coordinating federal education initiatives and funding programs 
for schools.  Provides some drug education program funding.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.whitehouse.gov/WH/EOP/ondcp/html/ondcp.html>
Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP)</a><br>
Office coordinated federal, state, and local policy efforts to control illegal drug abuse, and 
devises national drug control strategy.
<p>
<li> <a href=http://www.whitehouse.gov/WH/EOP/ondcp/html/prevent.html>
ONDCP Priorities for Prevention </a>
<p>
<li><a href=gopher://ncjrs.aspensys.com:71/11/drugs>
ONDCP Drugs and Crime Clearinghouse Gopher (Office of National Drug Control Policy) 
</a><br>
Gopher service for the Drugs and Crime Clearinghouse
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://ncjrs.aspensys.com:81/ncjrshome.html>
National Criminal Justice Reference Services</a><br>
Note:  Adobe Acrobat Reader software (may be downloaded free from this site is required to 
view and print some of the reports available at this site.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.nalusda.gov:8088/jg/pavnet.htm>
PAVNET: Partnership Against Violence Network</a><br>
Partnership of 7 cabinet-level federal agency programs against violence.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.fbi.gov/>
Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI)</a><br>
The nation's lead law enforcement agency.  Crime statistics, etc.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.usdoj.gov/dea/deahome.html>
Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA)</a><br>
The nation's lead agency for drug law enforcement.
<p>
<li> <a href=http://www.ustreas.gov/treasury/bureaus/customs/customs.html>
U.S. Customs Service
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.pueblo.gsa.gov/>
Consumer Information Center - Pueblo, Colorado</a><br>
Consumer information and government document distribution center.
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.dot.gov>
U.S. Department of Transportation</a><br>
Main WWW home page for the U.S. Department of Transportation
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.dot.gov/affairs/nhtsain.htm>
National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Public Inormation Page</a><br>
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.house.gov>
U.S. House of Representatives WWW Page</a><br>
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://thomas.loc.gov>
THOMAS - Federal Legislation Information Service</a><br>
Library of Congress WWW page, legislative information presented "in the spirit of Thomas 
Jefferson"
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://www.whitehouse.gov>
White House WWW Page</a><br>
WWW connection to the President and Vice President
<p>
<LI> <a href=http://ssdc.ucsd.edu/gpo/multi.html>
Federal Register and U.S. Code On-line - via Univ of Calif. San Diego
<p></a>
<LI> <a href=http://thorplus.lib.purdue.edu/gpo/>
Federal Register and U.S. Code On-line - via Purdue University
	<p></a>
<LI> <a href=http://www.cdc.gov/epo/mmwr/mmwr.html>
Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report (full text)</a><br>
Note:  Adobe Acrobat Reader software (may be downloaded free from this site) required to 
view and print some of the issues and files at this site
</ul>
</b>
<p>
<p>
<a href=http://www.drugs.indiana.edu>[IPRC  Home Page]

                
<p>
<hr>


