<h2>Alcohol, Tobacco, and Other Drug Prevention Resources</h2>
<p>
<hr noshade>
<a href=#Teachers>Links for Teachers </a><br>
<a href=#HigherEd>Prevention in Higher Education </a> <br>
<a href=#violent>Violence Prevention, Injury Prevention, and Safety Resources </a> <br>
<a href=#libsites>Websites for ATOD Prevention Librarians </a> <br>
<a href=#intl>International ATOD Prevention Websites </a> <br>
<a href=#programs>Prevention Programs and Materials </a> <br>
<a href=#on-line>On-Line Journals and Newsletters </a> <br>


<b>
<ul>
<li> <a href= http://www.drugs.indiana.edu/profiles/home.html>
Prevention PRO-files</a><br></b>
     Indiana Prevention Resource Center's on-line directory of nearly 2000 local drug 
     prevention programs in or serving Indiana, searchable by keyword.

<li> <a href= http://www.indiana.edu/~idap/index.html>
Indiana University Institute for Drug Abuse Prevention</a><br>
     Indiana University's drug prevention research institute.

<li> <a href= http://www.indiana.edu:80/~aids/>
Rural Center for the Study and Promotion of HIV/STD Prevention</a><br>

<li> <a href= http://www.health.org>
National Clearinghouse for Alcohol and Drug Information</a><br>

<li> <a href= http://www.arf.org>
Addiction Research Foundation </a>

<li> <a href= http://www.ed.gov/pubs/TeachersGuide/pt19h.html>
Drug-Free Schools and Communities Regional Centers</a><br>
     Drug-free schools and communities regional centers funded by the U.S. Department of 
     Education.

<li> <a href= http://www.bsos.umd.edu/cesar/cesar.html>
CESAR - Center for Substance Abuse Research (Univ. of Maryland)

<li> <a href= http://www.ria.org>
Research Institute on Addictions </a>

<li> <a href= http://www.uky.edu/RGS/PreventionResearch/>
Center for Prevention Research (Univ. of Kentucky) </a>

<li> <a href="http://freenet.vcu.edu/health/vatc/vatc.html">
Virginia Addiction Training Center</a>
     
<li> <a href="http://www.rci.rutgers.edu/~shaver/">
Rutgers Univ. Center of Alcohol Studies </a>

<li> <a href="http://showme.missouri.edu/~adaptwww/">
Project ADAPT:  Alcohol and Drug Abuse Prevention Team </a> Univ. of Missouri

<li> <a href=http://www.casacolumbia.org>
Center on Addiction and Substance Abuse </a> (Columbia University)

<li> <a href=http://www.rci.rutgers.edu/~cas2/>
Rutgers Center of Alcohol Studies </a>

<li> <a href=http://www.isr.umich.edu/src/mtf/>
Monitoring the Future Project </a> Univ. of Michigan Instutute for Social Research <br>
(National High School Surveys)

<li> <a href="gopher://gopher.nwrel.org:70/11/programs/drugfree">
Western Regional Center for Drug-Free Schools and Communities Gopher</a><br>

<li> <a href="http://www.ed.gov/pubs/TeachersGuide/">
Education Clearinghouses Funded by U.S. Department of Education</a><br>

<li> <a href="gopher://gopher.ed.gov/11/programs/NDN">
National Diffusion Network</a><br>
A  national  network  for diffusion and adoption of 200+ nationally  validated  education  pro-
grams.<br>

<li> <a href= gopher://gopher.ed.gov:70/00/programs/NDN/edprog94/eptw9>
Health Education Programs of the National Diffusion Network</a><br>

<li> <a href= http://www.jointogether.org/jointogether.html>
Join Together (a national graassroots prevention network)</a><br>

<li> <a href= http://www.ncrel.org/ncrel/sdrs/areas/sa0cont.htm>
Safe & Drug-Free Schools Programs at NCREL</a><br>from the North Central  Regional 
Educational Laboratory<br>
<li> <a href= gopher://gopher.cic.net:3015/11/>
NCREL's Safe & Drug-Free Schools Gopher</a><br>

<li> <a href= gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org:7003/00/ta/coal/53>
Drug-Free Schools Recognition Program

<li> <a href= http://fsci.umn.edu/cyfc/cyfc.html>
Children Youth and Family Clearinghouse - Univ. of Minnesota</a><br>

<li> <a href= http://www.well.com/user/woa>
Web of Addiction</a><br>

<li> <a href=http://www.amdahl.com/ext/iacp>
