<!DOCTYPE NETSCAPE-Bookmark-file-1>

<TITLE>'s Reference Information</TITLE>
<H1>SUGGESTIONS TO HELP YOU WITH YOUR RESEARCH</H1> 

<H2>WEB MANAGEMENT</h2>
<p>
The following web addresses may be helpful to you in your work:</p>
To find newsgroups, try<BR><I>Internet Newsgroups</I> at<br>
<a href="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/News/Groups/Overview.html"> 
HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/News/Groups/Overview.html"</a></p> 

<p>To get information on how to make the most of the internet try the<br>
<I>Big Dummy's Guide to the Internet - Table of Contents</I> at:<br>
<a href="http://www.cs.yale.edu/HTML/WORLD/org/eff/bdgtti-1.04/bdgtti-1.04_toc.html">
HREF="http://www.cs.yale.edu/HTML/WORLD/org/eff/bdgtti-1.04/bdgtti-1.0
4_toc.html"</a></p>

<p>To get help for creating a homepage on the web try:<br><I>Creating a
Personal WWW Home Page at IUB </I> at<br>                   
<a href="http://www.indiana.edu/ip/ip_support/www_personal.html">
HREF="http://www.indiana.edu/ip/ip_support/www_personal.html" </a></p>

<p>For general guides to how to make the most use of resources on the web
try: <br><I>The Guide to Network Resource Tools - World-Wide Web</I> 
at<br>
<a HREF="http://www.earn.net/gnrt/www.html">
HREF="http://www.earn.net/gnrt/www.html"</a> </p>

<p>If you're looking for a dictionary, try:<br><I>Hypertext Webster's
Dictionary Interface</I> at: <br>
<a HREF="http://c.gp.cs.cmu.edu:5103/prog/webster?">
HREF="http://c.gp.cs.cmu.edu:5103/prog/webster?"</a> </p>
           
<p>For a catalog of internet resources try<br><I>Welcome to the WHOLE 
INTERNET CATALOG</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.gnn.com/gnn/wic/">
HREF="http://www.gnn.com/gnn/wic/" </a></p>
<HR>
<H3>WEB SEARCH TOOLS</H3>

<p>To search for a term, agency, or whatever, on the web try either of
the following:<br>
<I>CUSI at Northwestern University</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.eecs.nwu.edu/susi/cusi.html#other">
HREF="http://www.eecs.nwu.edu/susi/cusi.html#other"</a><br>
or<br>   
<I>The Gopher of the ...</I> at: <br>
<a HREF="gopher://chronicle.merit.edu:/70/11/.ads/.ads-by...">
HREF="gopher://chronicle.merit.edu:/70/11/.ads/.ads-by..."</a> </P>

<p>Of special interest for Indiana information is the<br><I>HoosierNet</I>
at:<br>
<a HREF="http://access.bloomington.in.us/">
HREF="http://access.bloomington.in.us/"</a></p>

<p>For information on health agencies, try <br><I>HHS Agencies on the
Internet</I> at:<br> 
<a HREF="http://www.os.dhhs.gov:80/progorg/">
HREF="http://www.os.dhhs.gov:80/progorg/"</a> </p>

<p>To access information/links on a search term of your choice try 
<br><I>Lycos, Inc. Home Page</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.lycos.com/">
HREF="http://www.lycos.com/"</a> </p>

<p>You can read the latest<br><I>Update from the Director of the National
Institute of Mental Health</I> at: <br>
<a HREF="http://www.nimh.nih.gov/">
HREF="http://www.nimh.nih.gov/"</a> </p>

<p>To search for any word across the whole WWW try the amazing<br>
<I>Webcrawler Searching</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://webcrawler.com/">
HREF="http://webcrawler.com/</a> </p>

<p>For everything you've ever wanted to know about www communications
try<br><I>Welcome to Web Communications</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.webcom.com/">
HREF="http://www.webcom.com/" </a> </p>

<p>To connect to public www servers (Commercial, Government Agency, or
University) try <br><I>World Wide Web Servers</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.eit.com/web/www.servers/">
HREF="http://www.eit.com/web/www.servers/"</a> </p>

<p>To access just about any subject, including AIDS, epidemiology,
medicine and pharmacy, try the<br><I>WWW Virtual Library Subject
Catalogue</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/bySubject/Overview.html">
HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/bySubject/Overview.html"
</a> </p>

<p>For a list of U.S. federal government WWW servers and government
agency servers use <br><I>Yahoo's Government Agencies Indices</I> at<br>
<a HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Government/Agencies/Indices/">
HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Government/Agencies/Indices/"</a> </p>
  
For a more generalized search tool to look for any term use <br><I>Yahoo's
Reference</I> page at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Reference/">
HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Reference/"</a> </p>

<p>To find out about newsgroups concerned with a topic you are
researching, look at this <br><I>List of USENET FAQs</I> in a dictionary
listing by topic at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/top.html#D">
HREF="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/top.html#D"
</a> </p>
             
<p>To access the gopher or other resources of the <B>Northwest Regional
Educational Laboratory</B> use<br><I>NWREL's Home Page</I> at:<br> 
<a HREF="http://www.nwrel.org/">
HREF="http://www.nwrel.org/"</a> </p>

<p>To search for resources on, e.g. "elementary education," from
the <B>Northwest Regional Educational Laboratory</B> use their search
screen <br><I>Searching NWREL On-Line Resources</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.nwrel.org/search.html">
HREF="http://www.nwrel.org/search.html"</a> </p>

<p>Another source for accessing government agency servers is<br>
<I>Government Agency WWW Servers</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://www.eit.com/web/www.servers/government.html">
HREF="http://www.eit.com/web/www.servers/government.html"</a> </p> 

<p>Purdue's search tool for accessing government publications via the
web is <br><I>GPO Access on the Web</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://thorplus.lib.purdue.edu/gpo/">
HREF="http://thorplus.lib.purdue.edu/gpo/"</a> </p>

<p>You can access the <br><I>Library of Congress World Wide Web Home
Page</I> at:<br> 
<a HREF="http://lcweb.loc.gov/global/">
HREF="http://lcweb.loc.gov/global/"</a> </p>

<p>For their online services use this address, <br><I>Library of Congress
Online Services</I> at:<br>
<a HREF="http://lcweb.loc.gov/homepage/online.html">
HREF="http://lcweb.loc.gov/homepage/online.html"</a> </p>

<p> Return to <a href="..">Main Menu</a>
</p>
