<p>
<blockquote>

<!-- Headline Start -->
Indiana Senate Passes Bill Making Possession of Tobacco by Minors Illegal<p>
<!-- Headline End -->

<pre>
<!-- Story Start -->
The Indiana Senate has passed Senate Bill 0006, which makes possession of
tobacco products by persons under the age of 18 a Class C Infraction.  A 
Class C Infraction is punishable by a fine of up to $500 plus court costs.
<p>
Current Indiana laws makes purchase of tobacco, or "accepting tobacco for 
personal use" an infraction, but the new bill makes simple "possession" of 
tobacco by minors illegal.  This provision will make enforcement easier,  
since intent is not an issue.
<p>
The Senate vote on final passage was 46-4.  It has been referred to the 
House of Representatives, where action is expected soon.
<p>
<a href=http://www.ai.org/bills/sb/sb0006.1.html>
Click here </a> to view complete text of amended version.
<p>
<p>


<!-- Story End -->
</pre>


<b>Date:</b>
<!-- Date Start -->
2/4/97<p>
<!-- Date End -->

<i>Distributed by <a href="http://www.drugs.indiana.edu">The Indiana Prevention Resource Center</a>.
