<p>
<H1>Prevention Primer</H1>

<P>The Prevention Primer is an excellent reference tool for prevention 
practitioners.  It incorporates the principles of a public health approach 
to preventing alcohol, tobacco, and other drug problems in its summaries of 
issues and strategies.  It provides a brief history of prevention efforts 
and an overview of key topics, issues, principles, and approaches that have 
proven successful.  The topics are indexed in alphabetical order, including 
a partial list of referenced publications available through NCADI.</P>

