<h2>Indiana Together:  Strategies for A Drug-Free Indiana</h2>
<h3><i>Governor's Commission for a Drug Free Indiana</i></h3>
<HR>

<P>
<B>LEAD AGENCY RESPONSIBILITIES</B> 
<P>
The Agencies listed below are charged with the responsibility
to initiate the action and follow up on the progress of the 94
recommended actions contained within this report:
<P>
ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGE COMMISSION
<P>
Recommendations: C5, C7, C17, C18 &amp; C21
<P>
BUREAU OF MOTOR VEHICLES
<P>
Recommendations: C19 &amp; C20
<P>
FAMILY &amp; SOCIAL SERVICES ADMINISTRATION-DIVISION OF MENTAL
HEALTH
<P>
Recommendations: B1., B4, C11, C13, C14, El, E3, E4, F10 &amp;
H3
<P>
FAMILY &amp; SOCIAL SERVICES ADMINISTRATION STEP AHEAD: THE INDIANA
COLLABORATION PROJECT
<P>
Recommendations: Al, A2 &amp; B 15
<P>
GOVERNOR'S COMMISSION FOR A DRUG-FREE INDIANA
<P>
Recommendations: A3, A4, B2, B5, B6, B7, B8, B9, B10, B11, B12,
B13, B14, C2, C3, C4, C6, C10, C12, C15, C16, C22, C23, C24, C25,
C26,
<P>
C27, E2, E6, E7, E8, E9, F7, F8, H4 &amp; H5
<P>
GOVERNOR'S COUNCIL ON IMPAIRED &amp; DANGEROUS DRIVING
<P>
