<!-- title image end --><h1>Local Prevention Coalitions</h1>
<h2>A Web Section about Local Prevention Coalitions</h2>
<img src="bar3.gif" align="bottom" >

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="+1">XI. Evaluation Plan:</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">Each "Coalition" and each "Services Program" shall participate in DMH's Evaluation Plan for the Local Prevention
Services Coalitions.  The Coalitions and Services Programs shall work with DMH's technical assistance contractor, the
Indiana Prevention Resource Center (IPRC) to implement their evaluation plans, and Contractors shall submit monthly
program attendance report forms completed by program staff and the anonymous drug use survey forms completed by
participating youth.  Contractors shall also submit quarterly summary report forms for outcome objectives evaluation data
for each Services Program.  All forms from Services Programs shall be submitted to the Coalition's Contractor in a timely
manner so that they are received by the Contractor no later than the 15th of each month.  The Contractor shall collate all
forms received from each Services Program and shall complete the required summary and transmittal forms and submit
them to the IPRC in a timely manner so that they are received by the IPRC no later than the last business day of each
month.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">The Division of Mental Health shall make determinations of program efficiency and effectiveness based upon the
program objectives prescribed below.  For their own local purposes, Coalitions and Services Programs are encouraged to
establish additional objectives, but only information on DMH-required objectives should be submitted to the IPRC for
DMH's assessment of the Coalition's and Services Programs' impact.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Coalition-Level Evaluations</u></font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">1. Each "Coalition" shall adopt the two, specified, standard process objectives listed below.  Process objectives are
program objectives that describe intended activities or processes to be conducted by the Coalition.  </font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">A. [Required].  By June 30, 1998, the collaborating member  agencies of this Coalition shall implement the ____ Direct 
Prevention Services Programs as described in the</font>

<p><font size="-1">Coalition's proposal.  [Insert number of programs in blank  provided.]</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">B. [Required].  By June 30, 1998, at least ___% of the  participating youth registered for each Direct Prevention  Services
Program implemented by the collaborating member agencies shall successfully complete the programs. </font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">2.  Each Coalition shall adopt the four, specified, standard impact objectives listed below measuring prevalence of use by
participating youth.  Impact objectives are program objectives that describe a terminal behavior related to use of alcohol,
tobacco, or other drugs, or of the direct consequences of that use.  For the purposes of this BAA, all Local Prevention
Services Coalitions and Direct Prevention Service Programs shall use the same, four, specified, standard impact
objectives measuring prevalence of use by participating youth:</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">A.   At the conclusion of the Services Programs offered by  this Local Prevention Services Coalition, the prevalence of
reported cigarette smoking in the previous month by  participating youth shall not exceed ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">B.   At the conclusion of the Services Programs offered by  this Local Prevention Services Coalition, the prevalence of
reported alcohol use in the previous month by participating youth shall not exceed ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">C.   At the conclusion of the Services Programs offered by   this Local Prevention Services Coalition, the prevalence of  
reported inhalant use in the previous month by participating youth shall not exceed ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">D.   At the conclusion of the Services Programs offered by  this Local Prevention Services Coalition, the prevalence of
reported marijuana use in the previous month by participating youth shall not exceed ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Services Program-Level Evaluations</u></font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">1. Each "Services Program" shall adopt the two, specified, standard process objectives listed below.  Process objectives
are program objectives that describe intended activities or processes to be conducted by the Services Program.  </font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">A. [Required].  By June 30, 1998, this Direct Prevention  Services Program shall implement the program as described in
the Coalition's proposal, and shall enroll a minimum of  _____ "targeted youth" in ____ program groups.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">B. [Required].  By June 30, 1998, at least ___% of the  participating youth registered for this Direct Prevention  Services
Program shall successfully complete the program.  </font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">2. Each "Services Program" shall adopt the four, specified, standard impact objectives measuring prevalence of use by
participating youth.  Impact Objectives are program objectives that describe a terminal behavior related to use of alcohol,
tobacco, or other drugs, or of the direct consequences of that use.  For the purposes of this BAA, all Local Prevention
Services Coalitions and Direct Prevention Service Programs shall use the same, four, specified, standard impact
objectives measuring prevalence of use by participating youth:</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">A.   At the conclusion of this Direct Prevention Services  Program, the prevalence of reported cigarette smoking in the
previous month by participating youth shall not exceed  ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">B.   At the conclusion of this Direct Prevention Services  Program, the prevalence of reported alcohol use in the  previous
month by participating youth shall not exceed  ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">C.   At the conclusion of  this Direct Prevention Services  Program, the prevalence of reported inhalant use in the 
previous month by participating youth shall not exceed  ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">D.   At the conclusion of  this Direct Prevention Services  Program, the prevalence of reported marijuana use in the 
previous month by participating youth shall not exceed  ____%.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">3. Each "Services Program" shall select at least two and no more than four "Outcome Objectives" from the
DMH-approved list of outcome objectives below.  Outcome Objectives are program objectives that describe intended
program outcomes measuring a behavior or characteristic related to risk and/or protective factors.  They specify a
targeted rate of terminal behavior by the participating youth.  Outcome Objectives may be measured by use of a "paper
and pencil" measure or by a "social indicator."</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Approved List of Outcome Objectives for Direct Prevention Services Programs</u></font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Conflict Resolution</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the _______________________________ Conflict Resolution educational package used
by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">Social Indicator In the ___ month period following completion of this Services Program, the number of reported
_______________ [specify type of incident, such as violations of the school conduct code, juvenile arrests, fights, etc.]
shall not exceed ___.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Refusal Skills/Resistance Training</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the ___________________________________ Refusal Skills/Resistance Training
educational package used by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Provision of Factual Information About Drugs</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the __________________________________ educational package used by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Gang Prevention Program</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the __________________________________ Gang Prevention educational package used
by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">Social Indicator In the ___ month period following completion of this Services Program, the number of
___________________ [specify type of incident, such as graffiti, wearing of colors, incidents of gang violence, etc.) will
not exceed ____.  [Use data from a specific ___ month comparison period prior to the program to set the target
objective.]</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Violence Prevention Programs</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the __________________________________ educational package used by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">Social Indicator In the ___ month period following completion of this Services Program, the number of reported
_______________ [specify type of incident, such as violations of the school conduct code, juvenile arrests, fights, etc.]
shall not exceed ___.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Peer and Social Influences Education</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the __________________________________ educational package used by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">Social Indicator In the ___ month period following completion of this Services Program, the number of
____________________ [specify the indicator of peer or social influences, such as number of alcohol or drug billboards
in a neighborhood, the number of pro-drug songs on the radio, etc.] shall not exceed ____. [Note: percentage may be
substituted for raw numbers.]</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Normative Education</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the __________________________________ educational package used by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><u><font size="-1">Structuring Leisure Time to be ATOD-Free</u></font>

<p><font size="-1">Paper &amp; Pencil By the completion of this Services Program, at least ___% of participating youth will "pass" the
standardized quiz included in the __________________________________ educational package used by this program.</font>

<br wp="br1"><br wp="br2">
<p><font size="-1">Social Indicator In the ___ month period following completion of this Services Program, the number of reported
_______________ [specify type of incident, such as reports of alcohol use at school social events, the number of cigarette
butts or empty beer cans on a playground, etc.] shall not exceed ___.</font>
