<HTML>
<TITLE>Indiana-Youth Drug Use Stats -- Indiana PRC</TITLE>

<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<h2>Indiana Together:  Strategies for achieiving a drug-free Indiana</h2>
<h3>Problem Indicators Table #7</h3>
<hr>
<p>
<b>7. Monthly use of alcohol, marijuana, cocaine, cigarettes, and heroin
by youth, ages 12-17.</b>
<p>
Significant progress in decreased rates of alcohol and other drug use seems
to have stopped in 1993.  Indiana students 12-17 years old report increased
use of cigarettes, marijuana, and inhalants, with little change in the
monthly use of alcohol, cocaine, and other drugs.  Use of heroin was not
statistically significant.
<p>
<p>
<center>
<b>Percent of Indiana Students Reporting Monthly Use by Drug</b>
