<HTML>
<TITLE>Drug Use by Young Adults Stats -- Indiana PRC</TITLE>

<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<h2>Indiana Together:  Strategies for achieiving a drug-free Indiana</h2>
<h3>Problem Indicators Table #8</h3>
<hr>
<p>
<b>8.  Monthly use of alcohol, marijuana, cocaine, cigarettes, and heroin
by youth, ages 18-25.
<p>
<p>
This data is not collected in Indiana as of fall 1994.  There is a significant
need for collection of this type of data.
<p>
<p>
<center>
<table>
<b>Percent of Youth 19-25 Who Used Drugs in Past Moth, Nationally</b>

<tr><th>Drug</th><th>1985</th><th>1991</th><th>1992</th><th>1993</th></tr>

<tr><td>alcohol</td><td>70.7</td><td>63.6</TD><TD>59.2</TD><TD>59.3</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>marijuana</TD><TD>21.9</TD><TD>13.0</TD><TD>11.0</TD><TD>11.1</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>cocaine</TD><TD>7.5</TD><TD>2.0</TD><TD>1.8</TD><TD>1.5</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>cigarettes</TD><TD>36.6</TD><TD>32.2</TD><TD>31.9</TD><TD>29.0</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>heroin</TD><TD>0.3</TD><TD>0.1</TD><TD>0.2</TD><TD>0.1</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>any illicit drug</TD><TD>12.3</TD><TD>6.1</TD><TD>5.2</TD><TD>5.3</TD></TR>


</table>
</center>
