<!-- title image end -->



<h2>Indiana Together:  Strategies for achieiving a drug-free Indiana</h2>
<h3>Problem Indicators Table #5</h3>
<hr>
<p>
<b>5. Emergency room visits involving alcohol and other drugs </B.
<p>
<p>
This data is not being collected statewide at this time.  Data from a selected
number of hospitals is available, but is not sufficient for this report.
Nationally, the number of Emergency Room Drug Abuse Episodes rose from
416,962 in 1988 to 425,904 in 1989, then declined to 371,208 in 1990.  In
1991, the latest year for which national data is available, 400,079
episodes were reported.
<p>
<p>
Source:  National Institute on Drug Abuse, Drug Abuse Warning Network.
<p>
<p>
<p>
