<TITLE>Indiana-Binge Drinking by HS Seniors Stats -- Indiana PRC</TITLE>

<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<h2>Indiana Together:  Strategies for achieiving a drug-free Indiana</h2>
<h3>Problem Indicators Table #9</h3>
<hr>
<p>
<b>9. Incidence of heavy drinking by high school seniors.</b>*
<p>
*[Editor's note:  Statistics presented are "prevalence" rates, not "incidence"
rates.]
<p>
Progress on this indicator seems to have reversed in 1993, and the statewide
rate of "binge drinking" (drinking five or more drinks on a single occasion
within the past two weeks) continues to be much higher than the national
average.  This data is available locally from school districts which 
participated in the "Alcohol, Tobacco, and Other Drug Use by Indiana Children
and Adolescents" 1994 Survey.
<p>
<center>
<b>Percent of Indiana High School Seniors<br>
Reporting Incidence of Heavy Drinking</b>
<p>
