<TITLE>Indiana-Average Cost of Street Drugs Stats -- Indiana PRC</TITLE>

<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<h2>Indiana Together:  Strategies for achieiving a drug-free Indiana</h2>
<h3>Problem Indicators Table #11</h3>
<hr>
<p>
<b>11. Average cost of street drugs.</b>
<p>
<p>
The Indiana Criminal Justics Institute began a system for multi-jurisdictional
task forces to report street costs of illicit drugs, using data from 
undercover buys.  This data does not account for purity or volume of purchase.  
A report listing task force purchases and dollar values is available.
<p>
<table border=3>
<tr><th>  </th><th>Cocaine</th><th>Cannabis</th><th>Crack</th><th>Hallucinogens*</th><th>Depressants*</th></tr>
<tr><td> 1993 2nd qtr</td><td>$79.58</td><td>$8.12</td><td>$68.41</td><td>$5.00/du</td><td>$3.45/du</td></tr>
<tr><td> 1994 1st qtr</td><td>$79.83</td><td>$6.49</td><td>$166.94</td><td>$7.71/du</td><td>$3.66/du</td></tr>
<tr><td> 1994 2nd qtr</td><td>$86.21</td><td>$4.62</td><td>$100.00</td><td>$5.00/du</td><td>**</td></tr>
</table>
<p>
* Measured in dosage units which may vary according to application and task force reporting.
<p>
** Only two task forces reported, rendering the data insignificant.
<p>
