<IMG SRC="injuryl.gif">

<TABLE WIDTH=100%>
<TR>
<TD> <IMG SRC="injury.gif"></TD>

<TD>
<CENTER><H1>ATOD Resource Guide:<BR>Injury Control</H1></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<IMG SRC="injuryl.gif">

<H3>From the Director of CSAP...</H3>
<B>
<P>Alcohol and other drugs (AOD) are associated with all sorts of injuries, ranging from the highly publicized  drinking and driving crashes to the less discussed falls, drownings, and suicides.  We at CSAP have compiled this resource guide to call attention to these unfortunate consequences of AOD. </P>

<P>Prevention specialists, criminal justice professionals, and community leaders will find dozens of resources in this guide to help them create safer homes, neighborhoods, workplaces, and recreational areas.  Working together we can cut the number of avoidable injuries substantially and protect our children, teenagers, and families from the dangers associated with AOD.</P>
<BR>
<I> ----Elaine M. Johnson, Ph.D.</I></B><BR>
<BR>
<EM> January 1995</EM>
<IMG SRC="injuryl.gif"><BR>

<H5><P>
The listing of materials or programs in this resource guide does not constitute or imply endorsement by the Center for Substance Abuse Prevention, the Public Health Service, or the Department of Health and Human Services.  The materials have been reviewed for accuracy, appropriateness, and conformance with public health principles.<P>
This Alcohol, Tobacco, and Other Drugs Resource Guide was compiled from a variety of publications and data bases and represents the most current information to date.  It is not an all-inclusive listing of materials on this topic.  This guide will be updated regularly, and your comments or suggestions are welcome.  To suggest information or materials that might be included in updated editions, please write to the National Clearinghouse for Alcohol and Drug Information, P.O. Box 2345, Rockville, MD  20847-2345, or to <A HREF="mailto:info@prevline.health.org">info@prevline.health.org.</A><P></H5>

Produced by CSAP's National Clearinghouse for Alcohol and Drug Information, Karen Zuckerman, editor, and Peggy Lytton, publications manager.  <P>

For further information on alcohol and other drugs, call 301-468-2600, 800-729-6686, or TDD 800-487-4889.<P>
<I>Please feel free to be a &quotcopy cat,&quot and make all the copies you want.  You have our permission!</I><P>
Inventory Number MS461

<IMG SRC="injuryl.gif"><BR>
