<BLOCKQUOTE>This brochure advises captains of boats to stay sober and to set safe drinking limits for their passengers.  The pamphlet states, &quotIn an emergency situation, a drunken passenger is about as helpful as an umbrella in a typhoon.&quot  A resource list for further information is also included.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<B>Just the Facts... Adolescent Suicide</B><BR>
Year:  1990<BR>
Format:  Fact Sheet<BR>
Length:  2 Pages<BR>
Topic:  Alcohol and Other Drugs and Injury Prevention<BR>
Target Audience:  General Public, Parents, and Educators grades 7-12<BR>
Setting:  Health Care and School <BR>
Readability:  Average <BR>
Availability:  Florida Alcohol and Drug Abuse Association Resource Center, 1030 E. Lafayette Street, Suite 100, Tallahassee, FL  32301-4559; 904-878-2196
<BLOCKQUOTE>This fact sheet looks at issues surrounding adolescent suicide and states that suicide is the second leading cause of death for teenagers.  It discusses how alcohol and other drugs contribute to self-destructive behavior and magnify existing feelings of depression, sadness, and loneliness.  Signs and symptoms of suicidal behavior are given, and suggestions on what parents and friends can do are offered.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<B>Drugs and Suicide</B><BR>
Year:  1992<BR>
Format:  Book <BR>
Length:  63 Pages<BR>
